# https://medium.com/@munbonecci/how-to-add-a-password-textfield-component-with-toggle-icon-in-jetpack-compose-46652d771833
# How to add a Password TextField component with toggle icon in Jetpack Compose
[](/@munbonecci?source=post_page---byline--46652d771833---------------------------------------)[Mun Bonecci](/@munbonecci?source=post_page---byline--46652d771833---------------------------------------)Follow7 min readJan 15, 2024[
](/m/signin?actionUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2F_%2Fvote%2Fp%2F46652d771833&operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2F%40munbonecci%2Fhow-to-add-a-password-textfield-component-with-toggle-icon-in-jetpack-compose-46652d771833&user=Mun+Bonecci&userId=619aaf280d1d&source=---header_actions--46652d771833---------------------clap_footer------------------)--

[](/m/signin?actionUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2F_%2Fbookmark%2Fp%2F46652d771833&operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2F%40munbonecci%2Fhow-to-add-a-password-textfield-component-with-toggle-icon-in-jetpack-compose-46652d771833&source=---header_actions--46652d771833---------------------bookmark_footer------------------)Listen

Share

On this occasion, we will create a component that will be useful for our forms where we ask the user to input a password. This component will include an option to show or hide the password with a button, as well as a simple validation to determine whether the password is valid or not.

> 
These validations to determine whether the password is valid or not may or may not work for you as they depend on the rules of your business. The important thing is to see the component in action, to take the code and tailor it to your needs.

First, Add the following dependency in **build.gradle(Module: app) **and** **sync your project. This dependency helps us to obtain the **icons** we need for the **Toggle button**.

//In compose BoMimplementation("androidx.compose.material:material-icons-extended")// Or if you are using .ktsimplementation("androidx.compose.material:material-icons-extended:1.5.4") Create a folder called **components**, and in that folder, create the **PasswordTextField.kt** class. And copy the following code.

import androidx.compose.foundation.layout.fillMaxWidthimport androidx.compose.foundation.layout.paddingimport androidx.compose.foundation.text.KeyboardOptionsimport androidx.compose.material.icons.Iconsimport androidx.compose.material.icons.filled.Visibilityimport androidx.compose.material.icons.filled.VisibilityOffimport androidx.compose.material3.Iconimport androidx.compose.material3.IconButtonimport androidx.compose.material3.MaterialThemeimport androidx.compose.material3.Textimport androidx.compose.material3.TextFieldimport androidx.compose.runtime.Composableimport androidx.compose.runtime.getValueimport androidx.compose.runtime.mutableStateOfimport androidx.compose.runtime.rememberimport androidx.compose.runtime.setValueimport androidx.compose.ui.Modifierimport androidx.compose.ui.graphics.Colorimport androidx.compose.ui.text.input.ImeActionimport androidx.compose.ui.text.input.KeyboardTypeimport androidx.compose.ui.text.input.PasswordVisualTransformationimport androidx.compose.ui.text.input.TextFieldValueimport androidx.compose.ui.text.input.VisualTransformationimport androidx.compose.ui.unit.dpimport java.util.regex.Pattern/** * Jetpack Compose component for a password text field with validation and visibility toggle. * * @param password The current value of the password text field. * @param onPasswordChange The callback to be invoked when the password value changes. * @param errorColor The color to be used for displaying error messages. * @param textFieldLabel The label for the password text field. * @param errorText The error message to be displayed when the password is not valid.

 */@Composablefun PasswordTextField( password: TextFieldValue, onPasswordChange: (TextFieldValue) -> Unit, errorColor: Color = MaterialTheme.colorScheme.error, textFieldLabel: String = "Enter your password", errorText: String = "Password not valid") { // State variables to manage password visibility and validity var showPassword by remember { mutableStateOf(false) } var isPasswordError by remember { mutableStateOf(true) } // TextField for entering user password TextField( value = password, onValueChange = { onPasswordChange(it) isPasswordError = it.isValidPassword() }, keyboardOptions = KeyboardOptions( keyboardType = KeyboardType.Password, imeAction = ImeAction.Done ), visualTransformation = if (showPassword) VisualTransformation.None else PasswordVisualTransformation(), trailingIcon = { // Password visibility toggle icon PasswordVisibilityToggleIcon( showPassword = showPassword, onTogglePasswordVisibility = { showPassword = !showPassword }) }, isError = !isPasswordError, supportingText = { // Display error text if the password is not valid if (!isPasswordError) { Text( modifier = Modifier.fillMaxWidth(), text = errorText, color = errorColor ) } }, label = { Text(textFieldLabel) }, modifier = Modifier .fillMaxWidth() .padding(bottom = 16.dp) )}/** * Jetpack Compose component for a password visibility toggle icon. * * @param showPassword Whether the password is currently visible. * @param onTogglePasswordVisibility The callback to toggle password visibility. */@Composablefun PasswordVisibilityToggleIcon( showPassword: Boolean, onTogglePasswordVisibility: () -> Unit) { // Determine the icon based on password visibility val image = if (showPassword) Icons.Filled.Visibility else Icons.Filled.VisibilityOff val contentDescription = if (showPassword) "Hide password icon" else "Show password icon" // IconButton to toggle password visibility IconButton(onClick = onTogglePasswordVisibility) { Icon(imageVector = image, contentDescription = contentDescription) }}/** * Extension function to check if the [TextFieldValue] represents a valid password. */fun TextFieldValue.isValidPassword(): Boolean { val password = text val passwordRegex = Pattern.compile("^(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\\d)(?=.*[@$!%*?&])[A-Za-z\\d@$!%*?&]{8,}$") return password.matches((passwordRegex).toRegex())}

## `**PasswordVisibilityToggleIcon**`** Function Parameters:**
**Function Parameters:**

- `showPassword`: A boolean parameter indicating whether the password is currently visible.
- `onTogglePasswordVisibility`: A callback function that will be invoked when the password visibility is toggled.

@Composablefun PasswordVisibilityToggleIcon( showPassword: Boolean, onTogglePasswordVisibility: () -> Unit)**Determining Icon and Content Description:**

- `image`: Determines which icon to use based on whether the password is currently visible or not. It uses the `Icons.Filled.Visibility` icon if `showPassword` is true, and `Icons.Filled.VisibilityOff` if false.
- `contentDescription`: Sets the content description for the IconButton based on whether the password is currently visible. If visible, it sets the description to "Hide password"; otherwise, it sets it to "Show password".

 // Determine the icon based on password visibility val image = if (showPassword) Icons.Filled.Visibility else Icons.Filled.VisibilityOff val contentDescription = if (showPassword) "Hide password icon" else "Show password icon"`**IconButton**`**:**

- This is a composable that creates a clickable button with an icon. In this case, its used to toggle the visibility of the password.
- `onClick`: The callback function to be invoked when the IconButton is clicked. It triggers the `onTogglePasswordVisibility` callback.

 IconButton(onClick = onTogglePasswordVisibility) { }`**Icon**`**:**

- Displays a vector image (icon) based on the `image` parameter.
- `imageVector`: The vector image to be displayed (visibility or visibility off icon).
- `contentDescription`: A description of the icon for accessibility purposes.

Icon(imageVector = image, contentDescription = contentDescription)The `PasswordVisibilityToggleIcon` composable is responsible for rendering an IconButton with an icon that toggles between showing and hiding the password, and it takes care of handling the related accessibility content description.
