## **Issue Fixed:**

### **Problem:**
- The `onForgotPasswordClick` was setting `currentScreen = Screen.ForgotPassword`
- But immediately after, the logout logic was checking `!authUiState.isLoggedIn` and forcing the screen back to `Screen.Login`
- This created a conflict where the ForgotPassword screen would briefly flash or not show at all

### **Solution:**
- Added `Screen.ForgotPassword` to the allowed screens list when not logged in
- Now the logic allows users to navigate to ForgotPassword screen even when not authenticated

### **Updated Logic:**
```kotlin
// Before (broken):
if (!authUiState.isLoggedIn && currentScreen !in listOf(
 Screen.Login,
 Screen.SignUp // Missing ForgotPassword!
)) {
 currentScreen = Screen.Login // This was forcing back to login
}

// After (working):
if (!authUiState.isLoggedIn && currentScreen !in listOf(
 Screen.Login,
 Screen.SignUp,
 Screen.ForgotPassword // Now included!
)) {
 currentScreen = Screen.Login
}
```

